FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(tre.abnormal_stem_termination,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Not abnormal' when 1 then '`0002 Abnormal (broken top)' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not the tree length was unnaturally terminated.
ATTRIBUTE_REF: SELECT ABBR as value, meaning FROM fs_fiadb_urban.ref_abnormal_termination;
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(tre.abnormal_stem_termination,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Not abnormal' when 1 then '`0002 Abnormal (broken top)' when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other' end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(tre.abnormal_stem_termination,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Not abnormal' when 1 then '`0002 Abnormal (broken top)' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other' end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(cnd.AFFORESTATION_CD,-1) when 0 then '`0001 No' when 1 then '`0002 Yes'  when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end
PRC_METADATA: Indication that a condition has no evidence of prior forest, but it does have evidence suggesting deliberate afforestation attempts (planted or prepared to promote tree establishment) to convert to forest in the current inventory cycle or since the last measurement.
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(cnd.AFFORESTATION_CD,-1) when 0 then '`0001 No' when 1 then '`0002 Yes'  when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(cnd.AFFORESTATION_CD,-1) when 0 then '`0001 No' when 1 then '`0002 Yes'  when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(tre.bole_stump_removed,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Bole removed' when 1 then '`0002 Bole and stump removed' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not the bole and stump have been removed from the site since the previous measurement.
ATTRIBUTE_REF: SELECT ABBR as value, meaning FROM fs_fiadb_urban.ref_bole_stump_removed;
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(tre.bole_stump_removed,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Bole removed' when 1 then '`0002 Bole and stump removed' when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other' end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(cnd.canopy_cvr_sample_method_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 Ocular' when 2 then '`0002 Sub-acre' when 3 then '`0003 Acre' when -1 then '`0004 Not available'else '`0005 Other'end
PRC_METADATA: The canopy cover sample method used to determine live canopy cover percent, live missing canopy cover percent, and number of live stems.
ATTRIBUTE_REF: SELECT ABBR as value,meaning FROM fs_fiadb_urban.ref_canopy_cover_sample_method order by value;
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(cnd.canopy_cvr_sample_method_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 Ocular' when 2 then '`0002 Sub-acre' when 3 then '`0003 Acre' when -1 then '`0004 Not available'else '`0005 Other'end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(tre.cause_of_death,-1) when 10 then '`0001 Insect    '   when 20 then '`0002 Disease   '   when 30 then '`0003 Fire      '   when 40 then '`0004 Animal    '   when 50 then '`0005 Weather   ' when 60 then '`0006 Vegetation'   when 70 then '`0007 Unknown   '   when 80 then '`0008 Silvicultural' when -1 then '`0009 Not available'     else '`0010 Other'end
PRC_METADATA: The cause of death for all trees that have died or have been cut since the previous inventory.
ATTRIBUTE_REF: SELECT ABBR as value, meaning FROM fs_fiadb_urban.ref_cause_of_death;
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(tre.cause_of_death,-1) when 10 then '`0001 Insect'   when 20 then '`0002 Disease'   when 30 then '`0003 Fire'   when 40 then '`0004 Animal'   when 50 then '`0005 Weather' when 60 then '`0006 Vegetation'   when 70 then '`0007 Unknown'   when 80 then '`0008 Silvicultural' when -1 then '`0009 Not available'     else '`0010 Other' end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(tre.cause_of_death,-1) when 10 then '`0001 Insect    '   when 20 then '`0002 Disease   '   when 30 then '`0003 Fire      '   when 40 then '`0004 Animal    '   when 50 then '`0005 Weather   ' when 60 then '`0006 Vegetation'   when 70 then '`0007 Unknown   '   when 80 then '`0008 Silvicultural' when -1 then '`0009 Not available'     else '`0010 Other'end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(cnd.cond_status_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 Forest' when 2 then '`0002 Nonforest' when 3 then '`0003 Noncensus water' when 4 then '`0004 Census water' when 5 then '`0005 Nonsampled' when -1 then '`0006 Not available'     else '`0007 Other'end
PRC_METADATA: Description of the sampling status of the condition class.

SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(cnd.cond_status_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 Forest' when 2 then '`0002 Nonforest' when 3 then '`0003 Noncensus water' when 4 then '`0004 Census water' when 5 then '`0005 Nonsampled' when -1 then '`0006 Not available'     else '`0007 Other'end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(cnd.cover_class, -1) when 1 then '`0001 Tree Cover' when 2 then '`0002 Shrub Cover' when 3 then '`0003 Herbaceous Cover' when 4 then '`0004 Non-vascular Vegetation Cover' when 5 then '`0005 Mixed Vegetation Cover' when 8 then '`0006 Barren' when 9 then '`0007 Impervious' when 10 then '`0008 Water' when -1 then '`0009 Not available' else '`0010 Unknown' end
PRC_METADATA: The classification of land cover on sampled conditions.

SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(cnd.cover_class, -1) when 1 then '`0001 Tree Cover' when 2 then '`0002 Shrub Cover' when 3 then '`0003 Herbaceous Cover' when 4 then '`0004 Non-vascular Vegetation Cover' when 5 then '`0005 Mixed Vegetation Cover' when 8 then '`0006 Barren' when 9 then '`0007 Impervious' when 10 then '`0008 Water' when -1 then '`0009 Not available' else '`0010 Unknown' end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(tre.crown_class_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 Open Grown' when 2 then '`0002 Dominant' when 3 then '`0003 Co-dominant' when 4 then '`0004 Intermediate' when 5 then '`0005 Overtopped' when -1 then '`0006 Not available'     else '`0007 Other' end

SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(tre.crown_class_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 Open Grown' when 2 then '`0002 Dominant' when 3 then '`0003 Co-dominant' when 4 then '`0004 Intermediate' when 5 then '`0005 Overtopped' when -1 then '`0006 Not available'     else '`0007 Other' end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(mtre.crown_light_exposure,-1) when 0 then '`0001 No Light' when 1 then '`0002 Top or 1 Side' when 2 then '`0003 Top and 1 Side' when 3 then '`0004 Top and 2 Sides' when 4 then '`0005 Top and 3 Sides' when 5 then '`0006 Top and 4 Sides' when -1 then '`0007 Not available' else '`0008 Other' end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(cnd.mapden,-1) when 1 then '`0001 Initial Density Class' when 2 then '`0002 Density Class 2' when 3 then '`0003 Density Class 3' when -1 then '`0004 Not available' else '`0005 Other'    end

This classification is based on the number of stems/unit area, basal area, tree cover, or stocking of all live trees, seedlings, and saplings in the condition that are not overtopped. Any density other than Initial Density is used as an indication that a significant difference in tree density is the only factor causing another condition to be recognized on the plot.
ATTRIBUTE_REF: SELECT ABBR as value, meaning FROM fs_fiadb_urban.ref_tree_density;

FUNCTION_NAME: case  when coalesce(mtre.dia,-1) = -1 then '`0016 Not available' when mtre.dia = 0 then '`0016 not measured' when mtre.dia is null then '`0016 not measured' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,2.99) then '`0001 1.0-2.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,4.99) then '`0002 3.0-4.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,6.99) then '`0003 5.0-6.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,8.99) then '`0004 7.0-8.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,10.99) then '`0005 9.0-10.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,12.99) then '`0006 11.0-12.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,14.99) then '`0007 13.0-14.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,16.99) then '`0008 15.0-16.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,18.99) then '`0009 17.0-18.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,20.99) then '`0010 19.0-20.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,22.99) then '`0011 21.0-22.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,24.99) then '`0012 23.0-24.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,26.99) then '`0013 25.0-26.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,28.99) then '`0014 27.0-28.9' else '`0015 29.0+' end
PRC_METADATA: Mother tree diameter binned in fifteen 2-inch classes, with the largest bin containing diameters 29 inches and greater.
SQL_SELECT: case  when coalesce(mtre.dia,-1) = -1 then '`0016 Not available' when mtre.dia = 0 then '`0016 not measured' when mtre.dia is null then '`0016 not measured' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,2.99) then '`0001 1.0-2.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,4.99) then '`0002 3.0-4.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,6.99) then '`0003 5.0-6.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,8.99) then '`0004 7.0-8.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,10.99) then '`0005 9.0-10.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,12.99) then '`0006 11.0-12.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,14.99) then '`0007 13.0-14.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,16.99) then '`0008 15.0-16.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,18.99) then '`0009 17.0-18.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,20.99) then '`0010 19.0-20.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,22.99) then '`0011 21.0-22.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,24.99) then '`0012 23.0-24.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,26.99) then '`0013 25.0-26.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,28.99) then '`0014 27.0-28.9' else '`0015 29.0+' end
SQL_GROUPBY: case  when coalesce(mtre.dia,-1) = -1 then '`0016 Not available' when mtre.dia = 0 then '`0016 not measured' when mtre.dia is null then '`0016 not measured' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,2.99) then '`0001 1.0-2.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,4.99) then '`0002 3.0-4.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,6.99) then '`0003 5.0-6.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,8.99) then '`0004 7.0-8.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,10.99) then '`0005 9.0-10.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,12.99) then '`0006 11.0-12.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,14.99) then '`0007 13.0-14.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,16.99) then '`0008 15.0-16.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,18.99) then '`0009 17.0-18.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,20.99) then '`0010 19.0-20.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,22.99) then '`0011 21.0-22.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,24.99) then '`0012 23.0-24.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,26.99) then '`0013 25.0-26.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,28.99) then '`0014 27.0-28.9' else '`0015 29.0+' end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(cnd.site_class_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 225+ cuft/ac/yr' when 2 then '`0002 165-224 cuft/ac/yr' when 3 then '`0003 120-164 cuft/ac/yr' when 4 then '`0004 85-119 cuft/ac/yr' when 5 then '`0005 50-84 cuft/ac/yr' when 6 then '`0006 20-49 cuft/ac/yr' when 7 then '`0007 0-19 cuft/ac/yr' when -1 then '`0008 Not available' else '`0009 Other'    end

SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(cnd.site_class_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 225+ cuft/ac/yr' when 2 then '`0002 165-224 cuft/ac/yr' when 3 then '`0003 120-164 cuft/ac/yr' when 4 then '`0004 85-119 cuft/ac/yr' when 5 then '`0005 50-84 cuft/ac/yr' when 6 then '`0006 20-49 cuft/ac/yr' when 7 then '`0007 0-19 cuft/ac/yr' when -1 then '`0008 Not available' else '`0009 Other'    end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(cnd.site_class_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 225+ cuft/ac/yr' when 2 then '`0002 165-224 cuft/ac/yr' when 3 then '`0003 120-164 cuft/ac/yr' when 4 then '`0004 85-119 cuft/ac/yr' when 5 then '`0005 50-84 cuft/ac/yr' when 6 then '`0006 20-49 cuft/ac/yr' when 7 then '`0007 0-19 cuft/ac/yr' when -1 then '`0008 Not available' else '`0009 Other'    end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(cnd.productivity_status,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Unproductive' when 1 then '`0002 Productive' when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end

SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(cnd.productivity_status,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Unproductive' when 1 then '`0002 Productive' when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(cnd.productivity_status,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Unproductive' when 1 then '`0002 Productive' when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end

FUNCTION_NAME: fs_fiadb_urban.NUTS_FUNCTIONS.spcdlabel(tre.spcd)
PRC_METADATA: An FIA numeric code and common name identifying the tree species.
SQL_SELECT: '`' || CASE WHEN REF_SPECIES_COM.SPCD IS NULL THEN '9999' ELSE lpad(REF_SPECIES_COM.SPCD, 4, '0') END || case when REF_SPECIES_COM.SPCD is null then 'Other or Unknown' else ' SPCD ' || LPAD(REF_SPECIES_COM.SPCD, 4, '0') || ' - ' || REF_SPECIES_COM.COMMON_NAME || ' (' || REF_SPECIES_COM.GENUS ||' ' || REF_SPECIES_COM.SPECIES || case when REF_SPECIES_COM.VARIETY is null then ')' else ' ' || REF_SPECIES_COM.VARIETY || ')' end end
SQL_JOIN: left outer join FS_FIADB.REF_SPECIES REF_SPECIES on (TRE.SPCD = REF_SPECIES_COM.SPCD)
SQL_GROUPBY: '`' || CASE WHEN REF_SPECIES_COM.SPCD IS NULL THEN '9999' ELSE lpad(REF_SPECIES_COM.SPCD, 4, '0') END || case when REF_SPECIES_COM.SPCD is null then 'Other or Unknown' else ' SPCD ' || LPAD(REF_SPECIES_COM.SPCD, 4, '0') || ' - ' || REF_SPECIES_COM.COMMON_NAME || ' (' || REF_SPECIES_COM.GENUS ||' ' || REF_SPECIES_COM.SPECIES || case when REF_SPECIES_COM.VARIETY is null then ')' else ' ' || REF_SPECIES_COM.VARIETY || ')' end end

FUNCTION_NAME: fs_fiadb_urban.NUTS_FUNCTIONS.SPGRPCDLABEL(tre.spgrpcd, tre.statecd, tre.spcd)
PRC_METADATA: The general grouping of similar tree species for the purposes of organization and reporting.
SQL_SELECT: '`' || CASE WHEN REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.SPGRPCD IS NULL THEN '99999' ELSE lpad(REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.SPGRPCD, 5, '0') END || ' ' || CASE WHEN REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.NAME IS NULL THEN 'Other or Unknown' WHEN REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.SPGRPCD = 37 THEN 'Cottonwood and aspen (East)' WHEN REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.SPGRPCD = 44 THEN 'Cottonwood and aspen (West)' ELSE REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.NAME END
SQL_JOIN: LEFT OUTER JOIN FS_FIADB.REF_SPECIES_GROUP REF_SPECIES_GROUP ON (REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.SPGRPCD = CASE WHEN TRE.STATECD IN (46, 38, 31, 20) AND TRE.SPCD = 122 THEN 11 ELSE TRE.SPGRPCD END)
SQL_GROUPBY: '`' || CASE WHEN REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.SPGRPCD IS NULL THEN '99999' ELSE lpad(REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.SPGRPCD, 5, '0') END || ' ' || CASE WHEN REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.NAME IS NULL THEN 'Other or Unknown' WHEN REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.SPGRPCD = 37 THEN 'Cottonwood and aspen (East)' WHEN REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.SPGRPCD = 44 THEN 'Cottonwood and aspen (West)' ELSE REF_SPECIES_GROUP_TREE.NAME END

FUNCTION_NAME: fs_fiadb_urban.NUTS_FUNCTIONS.spcdlatinlabel(tre.spcd)
PRC_METADATA: An FIA numeric code and scientific name identifying the tree species.
SQL_SELECT: '`' || CASE WHEN REF_SPECIES_SCI.SPCD IS NULL THEN '9999' ELSE lpad(REF_SPECIES_SCI.SPCD, 4, '0') END || case when REF_SPECIES_SCI.SPCD is null then 'Other or Unknown' else ' SPCD ' || LPAD(REF_SPECIES_SCI.SPCD, 4, '0') || ' - ' || REF_SPECIES_SCI.COMMON_NAME || ' (' || REF_SPECIES_SCI.GENUS ||' ' || REF_SPECIES_SCI.SPECIES || case when REF_SPECIES_SCI.VARIETY is null then ')' else ' ' || REF_SPECIES_SCI.VARIETY || ')' end end
SQL_JOIN: left outer join FS_FIADB.REF_SPECIES REF_SPECIES on (TRE.SPCD = REF_SPECIES_SCI.SPCD)
SQL_GROUPBY: '`' || CASE WHEN REF_SPECIES_SCI.SPCD IS NULL THEN '9999' ELSE lpad(REF_SPECIES_SCI.SPCD, 4, '0') END || case when REF_SPECIES_SCI.SPCD is null then 'Other or Unknown' else ' SPCD ' || LPAD(REF_SPECIES_SCI.SPCD, 4, '0') || ' - ' || REF_SPECIES_SCI.COMMON_NAME || ' (' || REF_SPECIES_SCI.GENUS ||' ' || REF_SPECIES_SCI.SPECIES || case when REF_SPECIES_SCI.VARIETY is null then ')' else ' ' || REF_SPECIES_SCI.VARIETY || ')' end end

FUNCTION_NAME: case  when coalesce(mtre.dia,-1) = -1 then '`0004 Not available' when mtre.dia = 0 then '`0004 Not measured' when mtre.dia is null then '`0004 Not measured' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,4.99) then '`0001 1.0-4.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,10.99) then '`0002 5.0-10.9' else '`0003 11.0+' end
PRC_METADATA: Mother tree diameter binned in 3 classes: 1-4.9 inch; 5-10.9 inch; 11 inches and greater.
SQL_SELECT: case  when coalesce(mtre.dia,-1) = -1 then '`0004 Not available' when mtre.dia = 0 then '`0004 Not measured' when mtre.dia is null then '`0004 Not measured' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,4.99) then '`0001 1.0-4.9' when mtre.dia = least(mtre.dia,10.99) then '`0002 5.0-10.9' else '`0003 11.0+' end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(tre.dmg_excess_mulch,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not excessive mulching is present. Excessive mulching occurs when mulch is piled high around the stem at a depth greater than 3 inches. Mulch can take the form of many different materials and is not limited to wood chips.
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(tre.dmg_excess_mulch,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other' end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(tre.dmg_excess_mulch,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end

FUNCTION_NAME: CASE WHEN rpd.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN COALESCE(rpdn.growth_habit,'Not available') ELSE COALESCE(rpd.growth_habit, 'Not available') END
PRC_METADATA: The growth habit of the invasive species, based on USDA Natural Resources Conservation Service PLANTS (Plant List of Attributes, Names, Taxonomy, and Symbols) Database.
SQL_SELECT: '`' || CASE WHEN RPD_GH.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN CASE WHEN RPDN_GH.growth_habit IS NULL THEN '9999 Not available' ELSE GHN.LABEL_ORDER || ' ' || GHN.growth_habit END ELSE CASE WHEN RPD_GH.growth_habit IS NULL THEN '9999 Not available' ELSE GH.LABEL_ORDER || ' ' || GH.growth_habit END END
SQL_JOIN: JOIN FS_FIADB_URBAN.REF_PLANT_DICTIONARY RPD_GH ON (ISPCND.SPECIES_SYMBOL = RPD_GH.SYMBOL) LEFT JOIN FS_FIADB_URBAN.REF_PLANT_DICTIONARY RPDN_GH ON (RPD_GH.NEW_SYMBOL = RPDN_GH.SYMBOL) LEFT JOIN (SELECT LPAD(ROWNUM,4,'0') AS LABEL_ORDER, GROWTH_HABIT FROM (SELECT GROWTH_HABIT from FS_FIADB_URBAN.REF_PLANT_DICTIONARY group by GROWTH_HABIT order by GROWTH_HABIT)) GH on (RPD_GH.GROWTH_HABIT = GH.GROWTH_HABIT) LEFT JOIN (SELECT LPAD(ROWNUM,4,'0') AS LABEL_ORDER, GROWTH_HABIT FROM (SELECT GROWTH_HABIT from FS_FIADB_URBAN.REF_PLANT_DICTIONARY group by GROWTH_HABIT order by GROWTH_HABIT)) GHN on (RPDN_GH.GROWTH_HABIT = GHN.GROWTH_HABIT)
SQL_GROUPBY: '`' || CASE WHEN RPD_GH.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN CASE WHEN RPDN_GH.growth_habit IS NULL THEN '9999 Not available' ELSE GHN.LABEL_ORDER || ' ' || GHN.growth_habit END ELSE CASE WHEN RPD_GH.growth_habit IS NULL THEN '9999 Not available' ELSE GH.LABEL_ORDER || ' ' || GH.growth_habit END END

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(tre.dmg_improper_planting,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not improper planted is observed. Improper planting occurs when burlap, twine, or root ball wires are not removed prior to planting, or when the tree root flare is buried.
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(tre.dmg_improper_planting,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other' end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(tre.dmg_improper_planting,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end

FUNCTION_NAME: CASE WHEN rpd.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN rpdn.common_name || ' (' ELSE rpd.common_name || ' (' END || CASE WHEN rpd.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN rpdn.scientific_name || ')' ELSE rpd.scientific_name || ')' END
PRC_METADATA: The common name of the invasive species, based on USDA Natural Resources Conservation Service PLANTS (Plant List of Attributes, Names, Taxonomy, and Symbols) Database.
SQL_SELECT: '`' || CASE WHEN RPD_COM.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN RPDN_COM.symbol || ' ' ||RPDN_COM.common_name || ' (' ELSE RPD_COM.symbol ||  ' ' || RPD_COM.common_name || ' (' END || CASE WHEN RPD_COM.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN RPDN_COM.scientific_name || ')' ELSE RPD_COM.scientific_name || ')' END
SQL_JOIN: JOIN FS_FIADB_URBAN.REF_PLANT_DICTIONARY RPD_COM ON (ISPCND.SPECIES_SYMBOL = RPD_COM.SYMBOL) LEFT JOIN FS_FIADB_URBAN.REF_PLANT_DICTIONARY RPDN_COM ON (RPD_COM.NEW_SYMBOL = RPDN_COM.SYMBOL)
SQL_GROUPBY: '`' || CASE WHEN RPD_COM.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN RPDN_COM.symbol || ' ' ||RPDN_COM.common_name || ' (' ELSE RPD_COM.symbol ||  ' ' || RPD_COM.common_name || ' (' END || CASE WHEN RPD_COM.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN RPDN_COM.scientific_name || ')' ELSE RPD_COM.scientific_name || ')' END

FUNCTION_NAME: CASE coalesce(ispcnd.is_maintained_area, -1) WHEN 1 THEN '`0001 Invasive species is in a maintained area' WHEN 0 THEN '`0002 Invasive species is not in a maintained area' WHEN -1 THEN '`0003 Not available' ELSE '`0004 Other' END
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not invasive species is observed in a maintained area.
SQL_SELECT: '`' || CASE coalesce(ispcnd_maint.is_maintained_area, -1) WHEN 1 THEN '0001 Invasive species is in a maintained area' WHEN 0 THEN '0002 Invasive species is not in a maintained area' WHEN -1 THEN '0003 Not available' ELSE '0004 Other' END
SQL_GROUPBY: '`' || CASE coalesce(ispcnd_maint.is_maintained_area, -1) WHEN 1 THEN '0001 Invasive species is in a maintained area' WHEN 0 THEN '0002 Invasive species is not in a maintained area' WHEN -1 THEN '0003 Not available' ELSE '0004 Other' END

FUNCTION_NAME: CASE WHEN rpd.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN rpdn.scientific_name || ' (' ELSE rpd.scientific_name || ' (' END || CASE WHEN rpd.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN rpdn.common_name || ')' ELSE rpd.common_name || ')' END
PRC_METADATA: The scientific name of the invasive species, based on USDA Natural Resources Conservation Service PLANTS (Plant List of Attributes, Names, Taxonomy, and Symbols) Database.
SQL_SELECT: '`' || CASE WHEN RPD_SCI.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN RPDN_SCI.symbol || ' ' || RPDN_SCI.scientific_name || ' (' ELSE RPD_SCI.symbol || ' ' || RPD_SCI.scientific_name || ' (' END || CASE WHEN RPD_SCI.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN RPDN_SCI.common_name || ')' ELSE RPD_SCI.common_name || ')' END
SQL_JOIN: JOIN FS_FIADB_URBAN.REF_PLANT_DICTIONARY RPD_SCI ON (ISPCND.SPECIES_SYMBOL = RPD_SCI.SYMBOL) LEFT JOIN FS_FIADB_URBAN.REF_PLANT_DICTIONARY RPDN_SCI ON (RPD_SCI.NEW_SYMBOL = RPDN_SCI.SYMBOL)
SQL_GROUPBY: '`' || CASE WHEN RPD_SCI.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN RPDN_SCI.symbol || ' ' || RPDN_SCI.scientific_name || ' (' ELSE RPD_SCI.symbol || ' ' || RPD_SCI.scientific_name || ' (' END || CASE WHEN RPD_SCI.symbol_type = 'Old' THEN RPDN_SCI.common_name || ')' ELSE RPD_SCI.common_name || ')' END

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(cnd.land_cover_class_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 Treeland' when 2 then '`0002 Shrubland' when 3 then '`0003 Grassland' when 4 then '`0004 Non-vascular Vegetation' when 5 then '`0005 Mixed Vegetation' when 6 then '`0006 Agricultural Vegetation' when 7 then '`0007 Developed-Vegetated' when 8 then '`0008 Barren' when 9 then '`0009 Developed' when 10 then '`0010 Water' when -1 then '`0011 Not available' else '`0012 Other'    end
PRC_METADATA: RETIRED. The classification of land cover on sampled conditions. These classes are no longer used and have been replaced by COVER CLASS in order to remove all aspects of land use and, rather, focus on land cover.
ATTRIBUTE_REF: SELECT ABBR as value, meaning FROM fs_fiadb_urban.ref_cover_class ORDER BY VALUE;
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(cnd.land_cover_class_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 Treeland' when 2 then '`0002 Shrubland' when 3 then '`0003 Grassland' when 4 then '`0004 Non-vascular Vegetation' when 5 then '`0005 Mixed Vegetation' when 6 then '`0006 Agricultural Vegetation' when 7 then '`0007 Developed-Vegetated' when 8 then '`0008 Barren' when 9 then '`0009 Developed' when 10 then '`0010 Water' when -1 then '`0011 Not available' else '`0012 Other'    end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(cnd.land_cover_class_cd,-1) when 1 then '`0001 Treeland' when 2 then '`0002 Shrubland' when 3 then '`0003 Grassland' when 4 then '`0004 Non-vascular Vegetation' when 5 then '`0005 Mixed Vegetation' when 6 then '`0006 Agricultural Vegetation' when 7 then '`0007 Developed-Vegetated' when 8 then '`0008 Barren' when 9 then '`0009 Developed' when 10 then '`0010 Water' when -1 then '`0011 Not available' else '`0012 Other'    end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(cnd.fia_landuse, -1) when 10 then '`0001 Forest land' when 11 then '`0002 Agriculture' when 12 then '`0003 Rangeland/Chaparral' when 13 then '`0004 Commercial/Industrial' when 14 then '`0005 Residential' when 15 then '`0006 Multi-family Residential' when 16 then '`0007 Recreation/Cemetery' when 17 then '`0008 Rights-of-Way' when 18 then '`0009 Other Nonforest' when 19 then '`0010 Water' when 20 then '`0011 Nonsampled' when -1 then '`0012 Not available' else '`0013 Other' end
PRC_METADATA: The current land use for a condition.
ATTRIBUTE_REF: SELECT ABBR as value, meaning FROM fs_fiadb_urban.ref_fia_landuse order by value;
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(cnd.fia_landuse, -1) when 10 then '`0001 Forest land' when 11 then '`0002 Agriculture' when 12 then '`0003 Rangeland/Chaparral' when 13 then '`0004 Commercial/Industrial' when 14 then '`0005 Residential' when 15 then '`0006 Multi-family Residential' when 16 then '`0007 Recreation/Cemetery' when 17 then '`0008 Rights-of-Way' when 18 then '`0009 Other Nonforest' when 19 then '`0010 Water' when 20 then '`0011 Nonsampled' when -1 then '`0012 Not available' else '`0013 Other' end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(cnd.fia_landuse, -1) when 10 then '`0001 Forest land' when 11 then '`0002 Agriculture' when 12 then '`0003 Rangeland/Chaparral' when 13 then '`0004 Commercial/Industrial' when 14 then '`0005 Residential' when 15 then '`0006 Multi-family Residential' when 16 then '`0007 Recreation/Cemetery' when 17 then '`0008 Rights-of-Way' when 18 then '`0009 Other Nonforest' when 19 then '`0010 Water' when 20 then '`0011 Nonsampled' when -1 then '`0012 Not available' else '`0013 Other' end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(cnd.itree_landuse, -1) when 1 then '`0001 Agriculture' when 2 then '`0002 Institutional/Commercial' when 3 then '`0003 Residential' when 4 then '`0004 Multi-family' when 5 then '`0005 Cemetery/Park/Golf' when 6 then '`0006 Transportation/Utility' when 7 then '`0007 Water' when 8 then '`0008 Unused/Other' when -1 then '`0009 Not available' else '`0010 Other' end
PRC_METADATA: The land use of the condition using categories developed for the i-Tree urban inventory.
ATTRIBUTE_REF: SELECT ABBR as value, meaning FROM fs_fiadb_urban.ref_itree_landuse;
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(cnd.itree_landuse, -1) when 1 then '`0001 Agriculture' when 2 then '`0002 Institutional/Commercial' when 3 then '`0003 Residential' when 4 then '`0004 Multi-family' when 5 then '`0005 Cemetery/Park/Golf' when 6 then '`0006 Transportation/Utility' when 7 then '`0007 Water' when 8 then '`0008 Unused/Other' when -1 then '`0009 Not available' else '`0010 Other' end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(cnd.itree_landuse, -1) when 1 then '`0001 Agriculture' when 2 then '`0002 Institutional/Commercial' when 3 then '`0003 Residential' when 4 then '`0004 Multi-family' when 5 then '`0005 Cemetery/Park/Golf' when 6 then '`0006 Transportation/Utility' when 7 then '`0007 Water' when 8 then '`0008 Unused/Other' when -1 then '`0009 Not available' else '`0010 Other' end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(mtre.is_maintained_area,'-1') when '1' then '`0001 Tree is in a maintained area' when '0' then '`0002 Tree is not in a maintained area' when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not the mother tree is located within a maintained area. Maintained areas are defined as those which are consistently being impacted by mowing, weeding, brushing, herbiciding, landscaping, etc. Examples include, but are not limited to, lawns, maintained shrub beds, rights-of-way, and manicured park areas. Examples of unmaintained areas are overgrown lots, small wooded areas, and riverbanks.
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(mtre.is_maintained_area,'-1') when '1' then '`0001 Tree is in a maintained area' when '0' then '`0002 Tree is not in a maintained area' when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(mtre.is_maintained_area,'-1') when '1' then '`0001 Tree is in a maintained area' when '0' then '`0002 Tree is not in a maintained area' when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(sdl.is_maintained_area,'-1') when '0' then '`0001 No' when '1' then '`0002 Yes'  when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not at least half of the seedling count for an individual species is located within a maintained area (seedling bole must be partially or fully contained within the maintained area to qualify). Maintained areas are defined as those which are consistently being impacted by mowing, weeding, brushing, herbiciding, landscaping, etc. Examples include, but are not limited to, lawns, maintained shrub beds, rights-of-way, and manicured park areas. Examples of unmaintained areas are overgrown lots, small wooded areas, and riverbanks.
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(sdl.is_maintained_area,'-1') when 0 then '`0001 No' when '1' then '`0002 Yes'  when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(sdl.is_maintained_area,'-1') when '0' then '`0001 No' when '1' then '`0002 Yes'  when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end

FUNCTION_NAME: fs_fiadb_urban.NUTS_FUNCTIONS.spcdlabel(mtre.spcd)
PRC_METADATA: An FIA numeric code and common name identifying the tree species.
SQL_SELECT: '`' || CASE WHEN REF_SPECIES_MT_COM.SPCD IS NULL THEN '9999' ELSE lpad(REF_SPECIES_MT_COM.SPCD, 4, '0') END || case when REF_SPECIES_MT_COM.SPCD is null then 'Other or Unknown' else ' SPCD ' || LPAD(REF_SPECIES_MT_COM.SPCD, 4, '0') || ' - ' || REF_SPECIES_MT_COM.COMMON_NAME || ' (' || REF_SPECIES_MT_COM.GENUS ||' ' || REF_SPECIES_MT_COM.SPECIES || case when REF_SPECIES_MT_COM.VARIETY is null then ')' else ' ' || REF_SPECIES_MT_COM.VARIETY || ')' end end
SQL_JOIN: left outer join FS_FIADB.REF_SPECIES REF_SPECIES_COM on (MTRE.SPCD = REF_SPECIES_MT_COM.SPCD)

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(mtre.is_riparian,'-1') when '1' then '`0001 Tree is in a riparian area' when '0' then '`0002 Tree is not in a riparian area' when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not the mother tree qualifies as a riparian river/stream tree. Such a tree is one that falls within 30 feet of the edge (mean high-water mark) of a stream or river. If a stream is intermittent, or no water is running at the time of plot measurement, the stream must have a naturally developed stream bottom to be recognized as a stream. Lakes, ponds, holding basins, and wet lands are not classified as riparian zones. Man-made ditches and canals used to funnel storm water during periods of high rainfall are not considered streams. However, some stream segments, especially in urban areas, may occasionally have cement sides and bottoms, and these segments, that are generally part of a larger stream network, are considered to be a stream.
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(mtre.is_riparian,'-1') when '1' then '`0001 Tree is in a riparian area' when '0' then '`0002 Tree is not in a riparian area' when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(mtre.is_riparian,'-1') when '1' then '`0001 Tree is in a riparian area' when '0' then '`0002 Tree is not in a riparian area' when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end

PRC_METADATA: The straight-line distance from plot center to the nearest improved road. An improved road is a road of any width that is maintained as evidence by pavement, gravel, grading, ditching, and/or other improvements.
ATTRIBUTE_REF: SELECT ABBR as value, meaning FROM fs_fiadb_urban.ref_horiz_dist_imprvd_road;
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(plt.road_dist_cd,-1)when 1 then '`0001 0-100 feet' when 2 then '`0002 101-300 feet' when 3 then '`0003 301-500 feet' when 4 then '`0004 501-1000 feet' when 5 then '`0005 1001-1/2 Mile' when 6 then '`0006 1/2 Mile - 1 Mile' when 7 then '`0007 1 Mile - 3 Miles' when 8 then '`0008 3 Miles - 5 Miles' when 9 then '`0009 > 5 Miles'  when -1 then '`0010 Not available'else '`0011 Other'    end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(plt.road_dist_cd,-1)when 1 then '`0001 0-100 feet' when 2 then '`0002 101-300 feet' when 3 then '`0003 301-500 feet' when 4 then '`0004 501-1000 feet' when 5 then '`0005 1001-1/2 Mile' when 6 then '`0006 1/2 Mile - 1 Mile' when 7 then '`0007 1 Mile - 3 Miles' when 8 then '`0008 3 Miles - 5 Miles' when 9 then '`0009 > 5 Miles'  when -1 then '`0010 Not available'else '`0011 Other'    end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(tre.dmg_root_stem_girdling,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not stem damage from girdling root is present. Stem girdling occurs when roots begin to grow around the main stem of the tree and cut off or restrict the movement of water, plant nutrients, and stored food reserved. Certain trees are more prone to this problem than others. Lindens, magnolias, pines, and maples (other than silver maple) are susceptible to root girdling.
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(tre.dmg_root_stem_girdling,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other' end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(tre.dmg_root_stem_girdling,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end

SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(sdl.is_planted,'-1') when '1' then '`0001 Planted' when '2' then '`0002 Natural' when '3' then '`0003 Not Sure'  when '-1' then '`0004 Not available' else '`0005 Other'    end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(tre.dmg_sidewalk_root_conflict,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(mtre.is_street_tree,'-1') when '1' then '`0001 Tree is a street tree' when '0' then '`0002 Tree is not a street tree' when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not the mother tree qualifies as a street tree. A street tree is defined as a maintained-area tree, natural or planted, that is located within 8 feet of the edge of a maintained surfaced road. Street trees also include all trees located in the space between the edge of the road and sidewalk, or within a median strip between roads. A "clover leaf" interchange is not considered part of a median. Therefore, tree growing within a "clover leaf" interchange would only be considered a street tree if they were within 8 feet of the maintained road. In general, street trees provide shade, aesthetic values, or serve as a physical barrier between the street and adjacent property. These trees will generally have a visible, physical interaction with the street via its root system, overhanging branches, or proximity of the trunk.
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(mtre.is_street_tree,'-1') when '1' then '`0001 Tree is a street tree' when '0' then '`0002 Tree is not a street tree' when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(mtre.is_street_tree,'-1') when '1' then '`0001 Tree is a street tree' when '0' then '`0002 Tree is not a street tree' when '-1' then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other'    end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(tre.dmg_topping_pruning,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not severe topping or poor pruning damage is present. Severe topping is the cutting of branches down to stubs or reducing the stem height by 25 percent or more. Poor pruning includes leaving stubs outside the branch collar, or cutting into the branch collar. Topping is usually done to reduce the total height of the tree, while pruning is done to reduce the over form or volume of the crown.
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(tre.dmg_topping_pruning,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other' end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(tre.dmg_topping_pruning,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(tre.dmg_trunk_bark_inclusion,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end
PRC_METADATA: Indication of whether or not a trunk-bark inclusion is present. An inclusion occurs when branches are not strongly attached to the tree. A weak union occurs when two or more branches grow so closely together that bark grows between the branches and inside the union.
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(tre.dmg_trunk_bark_inclusion,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available' else '`0004 Other' end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(tre.dmg_trunk_bark_inclusion,-1) when 0 then '`0001 Absent' when 1 then '`0002 Present' when -1 then '`0003 Not available'else '`0004 Other'end

FUNCTION_NAME: case coalesce(plt.water_cd,-1)when 0 then '`0001 None' when 1 then '`0002 Stream pond' when 2 then '`0003 Swamp bog marsh' when 3 then '`0004 Ditch canal' when 4 then '`0005 Temporary stream' when 5 then '`0006 Flood zone' when 9 then '`0007 Other water' when -1 then '`0008 Not available' else '`0009 Other'    end
PRC_METADATA: The water body less than 1 acre in size or a stream less than 30 feet wide that has the greatest impact on the area within the accessible forest/nonforest land portion of the plot. Recorded waterbodies are listed in order from large permanent water to temporary water. This attribute is not recorded for water that is already defined as a separate noncensus or census water condition.
ATTRIBUTE_REF: SELECT ABBR as value, meaning FROM fs_fiadb_urban.ref_water_on_plot;
SQL_SELECT: case coalesce(plt.water_cd,-1)when 0 then '`0001 None' when 1 then '`0002 Stream pond' when 2 then '`0003 Swamp bog marsh' when 3 then '`0004 Ditch canal' when 4 then '`0005 Temporary stream' when 5 then '`0006 Flood zone' when 9 then '`0007 Other water' when -1 then '`0008 Not available' else '`0009 Other'    end
SQL_GROUPBY: case coalesce(plt.water_cd,-1)when 0 then '`0001 None' when 1 then '`0002 Stream pond' when 2 then '`0003 Swamp bog marsh' when 3 then '`0004 Ditch canal' when 4 then '`0005 Temporary stream' when 5 then '`0006 Flood zone' when 9 then '`0007 Other water' when -1 then '`0008 Not available' else '`0009 Other'    end
